ttps://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2017/07/Facebook-logo-on-mobile-595x400.jpg 595w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> Over 2.5 million unique South African browsers visit MyBroadband each month. These readers view over 9 million pages every month and engage in a ton of commenting and content sharing. This makes MyBroadband by far the largest ICT news website in the country, serving both business and consumer audiences. <img class="aligncenter wp-image-335968 size-large" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Websites-640x288.png" alt="Websites" width="640" height="288" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Websites-640x288.png 640w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Websites-600x270.png 600w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Websites-768x346.png 768w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Websites-1200x541.png 1200w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Websites.png 1221w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> According to feedback from South African professionals, online articles and reviews are the most-used and most-trusted marketing channels for purchasing decisions. What this means is that before an IT professional buys a product or service, they are almost guaranteed to first read an online article or review before making a decision. These findings were included in the 2020 South African Tech Marketing Report, which can accessed here. <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-335920" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Article-Audience.jpg" alt="Article Audience" width="640" height="430" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Article-Audience.jpg 640w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-conte